From: bay@eosdev1.gsfc.nasa.gov (John Bay)
Subject: Re: Recommendation of books on Tcl/Tk
Date: 15 Sep 1993 17:45:34 GMT

In article <2759as$npr@usenet.mcs.kent.edu>, wzhao@mcs.kent.edu (Weimin Zhao) writes:
> Could someone recommend me books on tcl/tk?  I'm trying to use it
> with Linux to develop some GUI applications.  Anyway, how is xview
> compared with tcl/tk?
>       Thanks in advance!   -Weimin
> 

What one might regard as the most definitive book on tcl/tk (since its author
is John Ousterhout, the author of tcl/tk) hasn't actually been published yet
to my knowledge.  However, its draft is available in postscript form from
harbor.ecn.purdue.edu in /pub/tcl/sprite-mirror.

