From: bf703@cleveland.Freenet.Edu (Patrick J. Volkerding)
Subject: Re: [ANNOUNCE] Slackware Linux 1.0.3
Date: 15 Sep 1993 23:32:55 GMT
Reply-To: bf703@cleveland.Freenet.Edu (Patrick J. Volkerding)


In a previous article, alan@qsss01.gs.com (Alan Buckwalter - x5586) says:

>does this new release have libc.4.4.2 ?
>i would like to upgrade, but I had lots of problems with the
>networking on the last release which had libc.4.4.1.

Nope. I'm hoping libc.4.4.2 will come out soon, and I'm not going to use
the alpha version in the meantime. I don't think releasing them in a
Linux distribution at this time is appropriate.

However, I have included a statically compiled rpc.portmap, and the 
librpclib_g.a library. This should cure RPC problems until the new libraries 
are released.

